Q. IS C++ a pure OOPS?
-> NO,because it uses primitive data type.

**OOPS->  Uses default data type.
OOPS is defined by 2 types:-
1.Class.
2.Objects.

Differenece between Class & Objects

                 CLASS                                             OBJECTS
   -> Blueprint/template of an object.               -> Instace(represent) of a class.
   -> Logical Entity.                                -> Physical entity.
   -> No space/Memory allocated.                     -> Space/Memory allocated.
   -> No physical existence.                         -> ***When an object is created only that time memory will be allocated.


**TYPES OF MEMORY:-
                STATIC/STACK                                                           HEAP/DYNAMIC
  -> Compile-time memory allocation-when depend on compiler                -> Runtime memory allocation-when depends on user.
  -> Less memory/space.                                                    -> More memory/space.
  -> Example:-                                                             -> Example:-
           int a;                                                                     int *a = new int;  new keyword is a keyword that 
                                                                                      gives you the address of that memory.

